<section xml:id="sec-escribed-circles">
  <title>Escribed Circles</title>

  <!-- Content summary: - Describe how these circles lie outside the triangle and touch one side and the extensions of the other two sides. (Mention that the center is formed by the intersection of two external angle bisectors.) - Demonstrate how to construct an escribed circle. -->

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Construct an inscribed, circumscribed and escribed circles on a triangle</li>
      <li>Determine the centroid and orthocentre of a triangle</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

